@Jane Wheelaghan 

First-year girls (HS) and women (college) are called freshmen as well, most of the time, although sometimes you'll hear freshwomen, too.  All-girl schools tend to avoid the word freshman, and stick with first-year student.  In some places, you might hear freshpeople to cover everyone, or freshers, or the very casual and somewhat dated frosh.

Co-ed is very dated by now, as nearly all schools are co-educational, and the females are just called female students, if the need to distinguish them from the males exists.  Females outnumber males now in most universities, so having a specific term for them seems silly.

